FT  28 JAN 92 / International Company News: Disney records profits up 22% in
first quarter
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN FRIEDMAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
EARNINGS from the recently-released film Beauty and the Beast and other
animated film and television products helped The Walt Disney Company to a 22
per cent rise in net income of Dollars 208.1m in the first quarter to
end-December.
The profits, on revenues 30 per cent up at Dollars 1.94bn, mark a recovery
for Disney, which ended its financial year to September 30 with a 23 per
cent slump in net income to Dollars 636.6m.
One of the problems facing Disney - flat attendance at its US theme parks -
continued in the first three months of the new financial year.
Operating income in the theme parks and resorts division dropped 18 per cent
to Dollars 113m, on revenues that were 6 per cent higher at Dollars 662.4m.
Increased costs associated with the 20th anniversary celebration of Walt
Disney World also contributed to lower operating results.
The filmed entertainment division managed a 49 per cent rise in revenues to
Dollars 965.8m in the quarter, with an 81 per cent jump in operating income
to Dollars 166.8m. These results reflected the success of Beauty and the
Beast in the US as well as the worldwide home video release of Fantasia.
The company's consumer merchandise division recorded 15 per cent higher
operating income of Dollars 88.7m on revenues that up 39 per cent at Dollars
308.4m.
Disney declared a 20 per cent increase in its quarterly dividend to 21 cents
per share. But Wall Street marked the company's shares Dollars 5/8 lower at
Dollars 132 1/2 .
