<TEXT>
BOEING, which is expected to complete the sale of its de Havilland division
in about a month's time, is to lay off about 317 workers at the Canadian
aircraft factory indefinitely, starting February 14, the company said
yesterday, Reuter reports. Boeing laid off 140 workers before Christmas. The
number of workers has shrunk from around 6,000 to fewer than 3,500 in the
past two years as recession has cut orders for its Dash-8 aircraft.
