FT  28 JAN 92 / International Company News: Statoil to boost refinery
capacity
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN FOSSLI
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   OSLO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
STATOIL, the Norwegian state oil company, is planning to invest an estimated
NKr4bn (Dollars 641m) to upgrade and expand European refinery capacity, and
is also seeking new capacity outside Europe, writes Karen Fossli in Oslo.
Statoil produces about 1m barrels of crude oil a day, but has just 200,000
barrels a day refining capacity.
It will spend about NKr2bn to boost annual refining capacity in Denmark to
4.8m tonnes from 3.5m tonnes by building a plant adjacent to its existing
refinery at Kalundborg. Construction will be completed in the fourth quarter
of 1994.
