<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JAN 92 / UK News (Employment): TUC will review Welsh economy
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANTHONY MORETON, Welsh Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Wales Trades Union Congress is to produce a review of the crucial issues
facing the Welsh economy.
It has commissioned academics from the University of Wales to produce
reports on subjects such as low pay, training, unemployment and relations
with Europe. The first report, on low pay, will be published early next
month.
Mr Kevin Crowley, Wales TUC chairman, said in Cardiff yesterday: 'Each of
the publications will set out clearly the waste of talent and resources that
has occurred over the last 13 years in Wales. This is the most comprehensive
review of the Welsh economy we have undertaken and it will point out the
shortfalls in government policy.'
Mr David Jenkins, Wales TUC general secretary, said the WTUC had 'a duty to
bring before the people of Wales a detached and thoughtful examination of
the record of the present government. There are areas of policy where the
government's record has been less than satisfactory. Our intention is to
produce background information so that the people can decide for themselves
whether they want change.'
</TEXT>
