FT  28 JAN 92 / International Company News: Outokumpu in FM750m deficit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HELSINKI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
OUTOKUMPU, the Finnish group, said yesterday its 1991 loss before
extraordinary items was about FM750m (Dollars 170m), compared with FM124m in
1990, Reuter reports from Helsinki.
The company said it expected the group's result to improve 'notably' in
1992. Turnover rose 12 per cent to FM12.7bn in 1991.
The end of 1991 was worse than expected. The last four months' result was
weakened by FM250m due to a poor market situation, foreign exchange losses
caused by the markka's devaluation and inventory losses on declining metal
prices.
