FT  28 JAN 92 / Management (In A Nutshell): The grand plan
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A course aimed at helping managing directors and chief executives of
companies in the Pounds 5m-Pounds 25m turnover range to develop and
implement a strategic plan is to be held at Manchester Business School
starting next March.
The course, Fostering Advanced Management Excellence, consists of 124 hours
spread over nine months and will involve business school staff helping chief
executives and their boards of directors implement the plans they have
produced.
