<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JAN 92 / Management (In A Nutshell): 3 ayes have it
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Britain's small firms should be queuing up to raise venture capital. Their
bankers are reluctant to lend and their balance sheets need a boost. In fact
the venture capital industry appears to be struggling to attract new
customers.
3i, the largest UK venture capital group and frequently a bellwether for the
industry, yesterday announced plans to target companies in the London area
with the launch of a Pounds 75m Greater London Growth Fund.
It expects to help 150 companies with sums of between Pounds 100,000 and
Pounds 5m over the next two years. Many growing companies are unaware that
long-term investment finance is available because of the venture capital
industry's emphasis on management buy-outs and the larger deals, 3i said.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
