FT  28 JAN 92 / Ulster accountant appears in court
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AN ULSTER accountant appeared in court in Belfast yesterday accused of
false-accounting offences dating back almost 10 years.
William James Johnston, 50, of Ballygallum Road, Downpatrick, faces charges
of falsifying financial statements and was freed on bail totalling Pounds
60,000.
Among the charges, Mr Johnston is accused of submitting false statements to
the Department of Health and Social Services and the Royal Ulster
Constabulary regarding the registration of four West Belfast social clubs
between 1987 and 1989.
Mr Johnston's lawyer said his client would be vigorously contesting all the
charges against him and he is expected to appear in court again on February
3.
