FT  27 JAN 92 / UK News (Employment): NUCPS may claim MoD guards
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LISA WOOD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE NUCPS civil servants' union said yesterday that it would expect to
recruit and represent Ministry of Defence security guards if their status
was changed to that of white-collar workers, Lisa Wood writes.
The union's intentions will anger the TGWU and GMB general unions, which
disclosed on Friday that about 2,400 military installation guards were to
lose the right to be represented by unions affiliated to the Labour party.
That is because the force is being reorganised and guards' status is to be
changed from industrial to non-industrial civil servants. The government
says political affiliation by a union representing non-industrial civil
servants runs counter to the Civil Service requirement for political
neutrality.
The NUCPS is not affiliated to Labour.
Mr Leslie Christie, NUCPS general secretary, said: 'We are not looking for a
fight with the TGWU, but if the end result is these grades are
non-industrial and linked to our pay scales, we would expect to recruit and
represent them.'
